<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" TextAlignment="Justify"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph>
This category contains samples that can be used to create large reports with custom formats.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples that can be used to create reports.
</Paragraph>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>External Connection</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how Essential XlsIO implement the connection between MsExcel and DB(MsAccess,SQL..etc).</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Import-Export Data Table</Bold> - This sample demonstrates importing and exporting data from a data grid using Essential XlsIO. This can be done with a single line of code, and you can apply custom styles when viewing the data in the data grid of an Excel sheet.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Import-Export CLR Objects</Bold> - This sample demonstrates importing and exporting data from CLR Objects using Essential XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>LINQ Wrapper</Bold> -This sample demonstrates how Essential XlsIO can be used in association with LINQ.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Template Marker</Bold> - This sample demonstrates the functionality of a marker that can be used to apply formatting.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Invoice</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how an Invoice can be generated for a given customer ID using Essential XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

</FlowDocument>